# Envoir self-host — example environment file.
#
#   cp deploy/.env.example deploy/.env
#   # edit deploy/.env
#   docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.yml --env-file deploy/.env up --build -d
#
# The only service in this stack today is `envoir-node`, which has NO environment-variable or
# config-file surface at all (its CLI takes a single subcommand argument and nothing else) — see
# deploy/README.md. This file is intentionally empty of settings; it exists so `--env-file` has a
# file to read and so `selfhost.sh` can seed deploy/.env on first run.
#
# The legacy SMTP gateway (which formerly read the GATEWAY_* variables here) now lives in its own
# repo, env-oir/envoir-gateway, and ships its own deploy artifacts and example env file.

# --- envoir-node: nothing to configure ---
# There is currently no env var or config file `envoir-node` reads. `serve-mail`'s ports
# (1143/1110/1587), its single demo login (owner@dmtap.local / app-password), and its in-memory
# (non-persistent) store are all hardcoded in node/src/main.rs. See deploy/README.md for the
# honest rundown and the port-publishing caveat.
